title: Haydn - The Paris Symphonies, Nos. 82-87 - Marriner, ASMF
description:
Haydn: The Paris Symphonies.

Joseph Haydn's Paris Symphonies, Nos. 82-87, recorded between 1975 and 1981 by Sir Neville Marriner and the Academy of Saint Martin in the Fields. This is the digitally remastered Philips Duo edition, released in 1993. These brilliant recordings of these inspired symphonies are perfect for those seeking modern instrument performances. Not to be missed by Haydn lovers.

Please enjoy.
